    "attributes": {
        "action": "Ban body shaming adverts, and fund a public awareness campaign ",
        "additional_details": "For example, a recent advert shamed those of a larger size for the serving size they take; this feeds into the fat phobia stereotype in which the size of one\u2019s body indicates their health.\r\n\r\nIf the Government instead funded a campaign to promote healthy relationships with food and exercise, I believe eating disorders would fall, people would be less likely to fixate on calories and ultimately, would have a balance, where food isn\u2019t viewed as \u201cgood\u201d and \u201cbad.\u201d We need to stop with the idea that a person\u2019s health is merely based on the shape of their body, and begin to teach people how exercise can be good for your health and well-being rather than aesthetics only. People should enjoy food and exercise, not fear it.",
        "background": "The Government should ban body shaming adverts, including for weight loss and diet products and services, which can create unhealthy eating and exercise habits. ",
